<p>Body fat is something we all recognize and in some cases obsess over. When trying to obtain our ideal physique, we look to reduce our body fat to make our muscles more visible. When trying to gain weight, we often look to pile as much muscle mass as possible.</p>



<p>However, measuring body fat can often be a time-consuming and expensive process depending on the method you use. Body fat calculators provide a non-invasive, easy-to-perform body fat estimation.&nbsp;</p>



<p>In this article, we teach you how the body fat calculator works. We also look at its importance when it comes to health and wellness.&nbsp;</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">How To Use This Body Fat Calculator?</p>



<p>To use the body fat calculator:&nbsp;</p>



<ul>
<li>Input your characteristics. These include your weight, height, age, and gender, as well as neck, waist, and hip measurements.</li>



<li>Click <em>Calculate</em> underneath to start the equation process.&nbsp;</li>



<li>The output gives you your body fat percentage, body fat category, lean body mass, and body mass index.</li>
</ul>



<p>The output information can inform suitable lifestyle choices and provide an easy reference point. It can be used anywhere with a mobile phone or a suitable gadget.&nbsp;</p>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start"><strong>How Does This Body Fat Calculator Work?</strong></h2>



<p>This body fat calculator works using scientifically proven formulas to estimate your body composition. The two primary methods used are the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6650177/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">U.S. Navy method</a> and the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4890841/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">body mass index</a>, or BMI.</p>



<p>By inputting certain body measurements, it works as a sophisticated tool to estimate your body fat percentage. Alongside this, it gives a few other useful readouts. These include your body fat category, lean body mass, and body mass index.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Input Data</strong></h3>



<p>To get started, you’ll need to take some measurements. Once you have done so, you can add these details to the calculator:&nbsp;</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>Gender: </strong>Male or female at birth.</li>



<li><strong>Age:</strong> In years.</li>



<li><strong>Weight:</strong> In kilograms or pounds.</li>



<li><strong>Height:</strong> In centimeters or inches.</li>



<li><strong>Neck measurement: </strong>In centimeters or inches.</li>



<li><strong>Waist measurement: </strong>In centimeters or inches.</li>



<li><strong>Hip measurement: </strong>Only for females, in centimeters or inches.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Output Data</strong></h3>



<p>Once the calculations are finished, the body fat calculator will give you these measurements:&nbsp;</p>



<ul>
<li>Body fat percentage.</li>



<li>Body fat category.</li>



<li>Body fat mass.</li>



<li>Lean body mass.</li>



<li>Ideal body fat for a given age.</li>



<li>Body fat to lose to reach ideal.</li>



<li>Body fat BMI method.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How Does This Tool Work?</h3>



<p>To calculate your body fat percentage, the calculator needs certain body measurements. For males, it needs your neck and waist. For females, it needs your neck, waist, and hips.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Following this, your BMI will be calculated using your weight and height. This provides a number that will fall into different ranges. Each range tells you if you’re underweight, a normal weight, overweight, or obese.</p>



<p>While it provides a quick and easy estimate, it can’t tell the <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/1660-4601/21/6/757" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">difference between muscle and fat</a>. Because of this, it may give false readings to certain populations. This is why taking body measurements is vital to provide a more accurate body fat percentage result.&nbsp;</p>



<p>With this data, the calculations are done using standard formulas. These consider the distribution of muscle, bone, and fat throughout your body.&nbsp;</p>



<p>They’re measured using the United States customary measurement system, or USC units. These are inches, feet, and pounds.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Body fat percentage (BFP) formula for males:</strong></p>



<p>USC Units:</p>



<p><strong>BFP </strong>= 86.010×log10(abdomen-neck) &#8211; 70.041×log10(height) + 36.76</p>



<p>SI, Metric Units:</p>



<p><strong>BFP </strong>= (495/(1.0324 &#8211; 0.19077×log10(waist-neck) + 0.15456×log10(height)) &#8211; 450</p>



<p><strong>Body fat percentage (BFP) formula for females:</strong></p>



<p>USC Units:</p>



<p><strong>BFP </strong>= 163.205×log10(waist+hip-neck) &#8211; 97.684×(log10(height)) &#8211; 78.387</p>



<p>SI, Metric Units:</p>



<p><strong>BFP </strong>= 495/(1.29579 &#8211; 0.35004×log<sub>10</sub>(waist+hip-neck) + 0.22100×log<sub>10</sub>(height)) &#8211; 450</p>



<p>The equations shown above provide estimates. This is because they are designed for general use rather than specific individuals.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Physical measuring tools provide a more accurate body fat measurement using methods such as bioelectric impedance analysis and <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6426203/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">hydrostatic weighing</a>.</p>



<p>Bioelectrical impedance analysis works by running small electrical currents through the body. With the electrical conductivity being different between body tissues, this can determine the percentage of body fat. While it&#8217;s more accurate than a calculator, it comes at the cost of convenience.</p>



<p>Hydrostatic weighing works by measuring body density in the air compared to the water. When the <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/316512210_Archimedes'_Principle_Revisited" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Archimedes principle</a> is applied, this allows you to see the difference between body components, including fat. Like bioelectric impedance analysis, it&#8217;s more accurate but much more time-consuming.</p>



<p><strong>Fat mass (FM) formula:</strong></p>



<p>FM = BF × Weight</p>



<p><strong>Lean Mass (LM) formula:</strong></p>



<p>LM = Weight &#8211; FM</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">BMI Method</h3>



<p>When measuring <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/370155448_A_Study_on_Body_Fat_Percentage_for_Physical_Fitness_and_Prevention_of_Obesity_A_Two_Compartment_Model" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">body fat percentage</a>, or BFP, you need to use your BMI and age. You input these into different equations depending on your gender and age. When done correctly, they should give you a body fat percentage estimation.&nbsp;</p>



<p>To calculate your BFP, use the formulas below:&nbsp;</p>



<p>Adult males: <strong>BFP = 1.20 × BMI + 0.23 × Age &#8211; 16.2</strong></p>



<p>Adult females: <strong>BFP = 1.20 × BMI + 0.23 × Age &#8211; 5.4</strong></p>



<p>Boys: <strong>BFP = 1.51 × BMI &#8211; 0.70 × Age &#8211; 2.2</strong></p>



<p>Girls: <strong>BFP = 1.51 × BMI &#8211; 0.70 × Age + 1.4</strong></p>



<p>The output from these formulas provides you with an estimate of your BFP. This can give you an indication of your general health when comparing the value to the reference ranges.</p>



<p>As mentioned previously, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC9977890/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">BMI can&#8217;t distinguish</a> between muscle and fat. Therefore, the reading may show a high BMI even though you have a low body fat percentage.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This is one of the possible disadvantages of using BMI as a health estimation. It can be used as more of a categorization for body index scales rather than a specific value.</p>



<p>If a higher body fat percentage is given, you should be aware of the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6348595/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">potential risks</a>. With a regular health check-up, you can learn more about the risks and potential steps you can take to limit them.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Body Fat Categorization</strong></h3>



<p>The benchmark for comparisons is broken down into essential fat, athletes, fitness, average, and obese categories:</p>



